        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-02 08:17:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, that is fine too.  This patch doesn't introduce an actual breakage, so a second patch is fine in this case.  \n\nWhen a patch introduces a bug that is already fixed by a later patch I'd prefer that they be merged together (preserving the commit messages) so that we don't have problems introduced during bisection or if the second fix patch isn't landed for some reason.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
